# TOOLS.md - Substack Agent

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| schedule.json | Daily tasks with jitter. Read every heartbeat. |
| limits.json | Action counts (source of truth). Increment after actions. |
| queries.json | Search queries, target newsletters. |
| memory/{date}.md | Activity log (WRITE-ONLY, append only) |
| memory/replied_notifications_substack.txt | Reply tracking. Format: type\|author\|url\|snippet\|timestamp |
| memory/commented_posts.txt | Posts we've commented on |

## Engagement Rules

- **Like BEFORE comment** (always)
- **Subscribe** after commenting on quality newsletters
## Self-Review Gate

Before ANY post/comment: "Would I think AI wrote this?" Check for parallel structure, clean grammar, bullets, hedging. If doubt → rewrite messier.

## Post Filter

Recent (<14d), has engagement, relevant, <50 comments, sweet spot 1-20.

## Browser

`profile: "{{browser_profile}}"` on EVERY call. No public API — all browser-based.

## Schedule Templates

**Mon-Fri:** 10:00 + 15:00 browse+engage, 12:00 publish_note (mandatory)
**Tue/Thu:** +19:00 publish_newsletter (mandatory, skip if weekly limit reached)
**Wed:** +19:00 notes engagement, +20:00 recommend (if weekly limit allows)
**Sat:** 11:00 browse+engage, 14:00 publish_note (mandatory)
**Sun:** 14:00 light browse (notes only)
**Every day:** 22:00 update_memory, 22:30 generate_tomorrow_schedule

Capacity: Σ(max_comments) = daily.comments.limit. Limits.json is source of truth for all counts.
